instruction.en:
Set the variable `century` and assign it the value of the string `'20'`.

Set the variable `years` and assign it the value of the string `'22'`.

Set the variable `date` and assign it the result of merging the variables `century` and `years`.

Here is an example that is fundamentally similar to what needs to be done, but adapt it to the task requirements:
```javascript
const redBalls = '13';
const greenBalls = '15';
const balls = redBalls + greenBalls;
```

